<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Greco-Buddhist_art&amp;action=edit&amp;section=32" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>"Religions and the Silk Road" by Richard C. Foltz (St. Martin's Press, 1999) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0312233388" class="internal">ISBN 0-312-23338-8</a></li>
<li>"The Diffusion of Classical Art in Antiquity" by John Boardman (Princeton University Press, 1994) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691036802" class="internal">ISBN 0-691-03680-2</a></li>
<li>"Old World Encounters. Cross-cultural contacts and exchanges in pre-modern times" by Jerry H.Bentley (Oxford University Press, 1993) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0195076397" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-507639-7</a></li>
<li>"Alexander the Great: East-West Cultural contacts from Greece to Japan" (NHK and Tokyo National Museum, 2003)</li>
<li>"The Greeks in Bactria and India" W.W. Tarn, Cambridge University Press</li>
<li>"Living Zen" by <a href="/wiki/Robert_Linssen" title="Robert Linssen">Robert Linssen</a> (Grove Press New York, 1958) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0802131360" class="internal">ISBN 0-8021-3136-0</a></li>
<li>"Echoes of Alexander the Great: Silk route portraits from Gandhara" by Marian Wenzel, with a foreword by the Dalai Lama (Eklisa Anstalt, 2000) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1588860140" class="internal">ISBN 1-58886-014-0</a></li>
<li>"The Crossroads of Asia. Transformation in Image and symbol", 1992, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0951839918" class="internal">ISBN 0-9518399-1-8</a></li>
</ul>
